text: This is a list of Fleet Air Arm squadrons. Squadrons in bold are currently active. == 700 series squadrons == 700-series squadrons are generally experimental or training squadrons, which produce trained aircrew for the operational 800-series squadrons. ==800 series squadrons== The 800 Series was allocated to carrier and land based operational squadrons of the Fleet Air Arm. == 1700 series squadrons == ==1800 series squadrons== ==See also== * List of Royal Air Force aircraft squadrons ==References== ===Citations=== ===Bibliography=== * ==External links== Fleet Air Arm *
